<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-10-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4992/13.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-10-09"><hi rend="italic">October 9,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Fletcher reports that the Chinese authorities at Mukden have been
                            instructed to surrender McKinley. He requests instructions by telegraph
                            as to custody.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>